---
import Header from '../../components/Header.astro';
import BaseHead from '../../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Footer from '../../components/Footer.astro';

const pageTitle = 'Best Budget Wireless Mouse for Work 2026';
const pageDescription = 'Honest review of the Uineer rechargeable wireless mouse. Under $20 with visible battery level and ergonomic design.';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <BaseHead title={pageTitle} description={pageDescription} />
    <style>
      main { max-width: 720px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 2rem 1rem; line-height: 1.7; color: #333; }
      h1 { color: #232f3e; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
      .meta { color: #666; font-size: 0.9rem; margin-bottom: 2rem; }
      .product-box { background: #f8f9fa; border-radius: 8px; padding: 1.5rem; margin: 2rem 0; }
      .product-box h2 { margin-top: 0; }
      .product-box ul { padding-left: 1.2rem; }
      .btn { display: inline-block; background: #ff9900; color: #000; padding: 12px 24px; text-decoration: none; border-radius: 4px; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 0.5rem; }
      .btn:hover { background: #e68a00; }
      .disclaimer { font-size: 0.8rem; color: #888; margin-top: 3rem; border-top: 1px solid #eee; padding-top: 1rem; }
    </style>
  </head>
  <body>
    <Header />
    <main>
      <h1>Best Budget Wireless Mouse for Work</h1>
      <div class="meta">Updated May 2026 · Under $20</div>

      <p>If you spend 8+ hours at a desk, a reliable wireless mouse is non-negotiable. After testing multiple budget options, one stands out for a simple reason: it shows the battery level directly on the device, so you never get caught with a dead mouse before a deadline.</p>

      <div class="product-box">
        <h2>🏆 Uineer Wireless Mouse</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Rechargeable 2.4GHz</strong> — no more disposable batteries</li>
          <li><strong>Visible battery indicator</strong> — 4 LED levels on the device</li>
          <li><strong>4 adjustable DPI levels</strong> — 800/1200/1600/2000</li>
          <li><strong>Ergonomic grip</strong> — matte finish, side thumb rest</li>
          <li><strong>8,600+ ratings</strong> · Amazon's Choice · $13.99</li>
        </ul>
        <a href="https://amzn.to/49eS8nX" class="btn" target="_blank" rel="noopener sponsored">Check Current Price on Amazon</a>
      </div>

      <h3>Why it wins at this price</h3>
      <p>Most $10–$15 mice cut corners on the sensor or build quality. The Uineer keeps a stable 2.4GHz connection across a full office floor, and the rechargeable battery lasts roughly 3–4 weeks of daily use. The visible battery meter removes the guessing game entirely.</p>

      <h3>Who should buy it</h3>
      <p>Remote workers, students, and anyone who wants a no-fuss daily driver without spending $40+ on a premium brand. It is not a gaming mouse, but for Excel, browsing, and document work, it is noticeably smoother than generic office mice.</p>

      <div class="disclaimer">
        Disclosure: As an Amazon Associate I earn from qualifying purchases. This review is based on independent research and reader feedback.
      </div>
    </main>
    <Footer />
  </body>
</html>